1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson we will briefly discuss how comments are displayed when you're using a block theme.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Before we make our way to the back end of our website, let's see how comments display when people respond to a blog post.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
When I visit the front end of my website, I will click on one of my blog posts.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:20,000
When we go to the bottom of the post, we will notice three people have already responded by adding their comments,

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Roger, Tina and Ross.

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
And below that, there is a section for more people to have their say.

7
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Allowing comments on your site has many advantages.

8
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,000
It allows you to deepen your relationships with readers and find out what readers are interested in.

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,000
It also increases the likelihood of them subscribing to your newsletter or purchasing something.

10
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,000
Essentially, allowing comments can help you build a community around your blog.

11
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
It is of course essential to manage comments effectively by using the built-in settings of WordPress under discussions in your dashboard and installing an anti-spam plugin.

12
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:04,000
You can also check out our video about managing spam.

13
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,000
The Comments block are generally added to the single posts template.

14
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Let's make our way to Appearance and click on Editor.

15
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Then, open up templates and select the single template or the single posts template.

16
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:23,000
And as we can see, our single template consists of a header, Content block and then Comments block.

17
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
And right at the bottom, a footer.

18
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,000
When we open the List View, we will have a clearer picture of all the nested blocks.

19
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,000
And within the Group block, we will see the Comments block.

20
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Have you ever wondered what will happen if you delete the Comments block?

21
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Well, all comments on all blog posts that have been assigned to this template will disappear on the front end of your website.

22
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,000
So, be careful not to delete this block.

23
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,000
So, to put it all in context, when I open up one of my posts, in this case The World is Your Oyster,

24
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,000
we will see the post on the left and on the right next to templates

25
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:10,000
we will see this post has been assigned to the single template.

26
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,000
And when I open the post on the front end of my site, I will see the structure that the template provides, as well as the Comments block.

27
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,000
But, what if you wanted to display comments on one of your pages?

28
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Well, you can open up the sidebar settings and below discussions select Allow comments.

29
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,000
To end off, I also wanted to mention the Latest Comments block.

30
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,000
The Latest Comments block allows you to display the most recent comments readers have left on your blog.

31
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Let's add this block to my home page to show you how it works.

32
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
So, below Feedback from our readers, I am going to add the Latest Comments block.

33
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,000
And to clarify, the block is not to add comments, but to display the latest comments readers have made across your entire site.

34
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:12,000
Each comment links to its original post, when it was left and who left it.

35
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,000
You can use your sidebar settings on the right to style the block further.

36
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,000
May you utilize the comments block to build a strong community or following on your site through feedback and dialogue.

